      "writtenOn": "2020-12-15T22:30:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I have a question here. Is it valid to not specify TlwPort? For ssh, port will be 22 if the port is specified. TlwPort will be 0 if it is not specified. That\u0027s why I have a check here. Please let me know if TlsPort must be specified. Thanks.",
      "parentUuid": "32b7b6c0_f3082ee9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 50,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "222e48f320a63990353bc78cc036616444c49fb0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e62f9593_6ec9a8c8",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/cmd/tast_rtd/invocation.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 50,
      "author": {
        "id": 1166720
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-16T02:19:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Now I have found it is actually valid to have no port number.\nTast passes the TLW address string as-is from the commandline to grpc.Dial(), and it is finally interpreted by GRPC library.\nAccording to the document, when [:port] is ommitted, it defaults to either HTTP or HTTPS depending on the channel.\nhttps://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/doc/naming.md\n\nAnd it may be still better not to hide error when negative number were wrongly given. If we don\u0027t return error here, how about checking by !\u003d 0 here so as to let GRPC library produce an error later?",
      "parentUuid": "e7a77106_e618cd88",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 50,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "222e48f320a63990353bc78cc036616444c49fb0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
